          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can use this property to change your application’s appearance before a snapshot is taken. For example, if the property contains an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKSnapshotReason/appBackgrounded",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " value, you’d probably want to capture the app’s current state, and no changes are necessary. However, if the property contains a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKSnapshotReason/returnToDefaultState",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " value, you may want to navigate back to the root view controller before taking the snapshot.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For a list of possible reasons for taking the snapshot, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKSnapshotReason",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
